Time Analysis

In the first visualization I want to look at is when during the day the most rides were scheduled

Rides separated by Booking Status

In[26]:
status_colors = {
    "Total": "brown",
    "Completed": "green",
    "Cancelled by Customer": "blue",
    "Cancelled by Driver": "orange",
    "Incomplete": "red",
    "No Driver Found": "#A219E1"
}

# Convert Time column to datetime
df["Time"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Time"], format="%H:%M:%S", errors="coerce")

# Round down to nearest 20 minutes
df["Time_20min"] = df["Time"].dt.floor("20min").dt.strftime("%H:%M")

# Count rides by 20-min interval and Booking Status
status_counts = df.groupby(["Time_20min", "Booking Status"]).size().reset_index(name="Number of Rides")

# Also calculate total rides regardless of status
total_counts = df.groupby("Time_20min").size().reset_index(name="Number of Rides")
total_counts["Booking Status"] = "Total"  # Add label so we can plot it together

# Combine into one DataFrame
plot_df = pd.concat([status_counts, total_counts])

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))
sns.lineplot(data=plot_df, x="Time_20min", y="Number of Rides", hue="Booking Status", palette=status_colors, marker="o")

plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.title("Number of Rides Scheduled (20-Minute Intervals, by Booking Status)")
plt.xlabel("Time of Day (20-min bins)")
plt.ylabel("Number of Rides")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Separated by Booking Status with a focus on cancelled/incomplete rides

For this visualization I wanted to focus on the lower portion of the above visual

In[27]:
# Define the statuses we care about
problem_statuses = ["Cancelled by Customer", "Cancelled by Driver", "Incomplete", "No Driver Found"]

# Filter dataset
problem_df = df[df["Booking Status"].isin(problem_statuses)]

# Count rides by 20-min interval and Booking Status
problem_counts = (
    problem_df.groupby(["Time_20min", "Booking Status"])
    .size()
    .reset_index(name="Number of Rides")
)

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))
sns.lineplot(
    data=problem_counts,
    x="Time_20min",
    y="Number of Rides",
    hue="Booking Status",
    palette=status_colors,
    marker="o"
)

plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.title("Problematic Rides (Cancelled, Incomplete, No Driver Found) by 20-Minute Intervals")
plt.xlabel("Time of Day (20-min bins)")
plt.ylabel("Number of Rides")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))

# Create evenly spaced bins between min and max
bin_edges = np.linspace(df["Customer Rating"].min(), df["Customer Rating"].max(), 11)

sns.histplot(
    df["Customer Rating"].dropna(), 
    bins=bin_edges, 
    color="skyblue", 
    edgecolor="black"
)

plt.title("Distribution of Customer Ratings")
plt.xlabel("Customer Rating")
plt.ylabel("Number of Rides")
plt.xticks(bin_edges, rotation=0)
plt.show()
In[58]:
ratings_over_time = df.groupby("Date")["Customer Rating"].mean().reset_index()

# Determine split points
n = len(ratings_over_time)
q1 = n // 4
q2 = n // 2
q3 = 3 * n // 4

# Create 4 subplots (stacked vertically)
fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 1, figsize=(15, 20), sharey=True)

# Quarter 1
sns.lineplot(data=ratings_over_time.iloc[:q1], x="Date", y="Customer Rating",
             marker="o", color="green", ax=axes[0])
axes[0].set_title("Average Customer Rating (1st Quarter of Dates)")
axes[0].set_xlabel("")
axes[0].set_ylabel("Average Rating")
axes[0].tick_params(axis="x", rotation=90)

# Quarter 2
sns.lineplot(data=ratings_over_time.iloc[q1:q2], x="Date", y="Customer Rating",
             marker="o", color="green", ax=axes[1])
axes[1].set_title("Average Customer Rating (2nd Quarter of Dates)")
axes[1].set_xlabel("")
axes[1].set_ylabel("Average Rating")
axes[1].tick_params(axis="x", rotation=90)

# Quarter 3
sns.lineplot(data=ratings_over_time.iloc[q2:q3], x="Date", y="Customer Rating",
             marker="o", color="green", ax=axes[2])
axes[2].set_title("Average Customer Rating (3rd Quarter of Dates)")
axes[2].set_xlabel("")
axes[2].set_ylabel("Average Rating")
axes[2].tick_params(axis="x", rotation=90)

# Quarter 4
sns.lineplot(data=ratings_over_time.iloc[q3:], x="Date", y="Customer Rating",
             marker="o", color="green", ax=axes[3])
axes[3].set_title("Average Customer Rating (4th Quarter of Dates)")
axes[3].set_xlabel("Date")
axes[3].set_ylabel("Average Rating")
axes[3].tick_params(axis="x", rotation=90)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
